Given that
$\frac 1{2!17!}+\frac 1{3!16!}+\frac 1{4!15!}+\frac 1{5!14!}+\frac 1{6!13!}+\frac 1{7!12!}+\frac 1{8!11!}+\frac 1{9!10!}=\frac N{1!18!}$
find the greatest integer that is less than $\frac N{100}$.

**Solution:**
$$=\frac 1{2!17!}+\frac 1{3!16!}+\frac 1{4!15!}+\frac 1{5!14!}+\frac 1{6!13!}+\frac 1{7!12!}+\frac 1{8!11!}+\frac 1{9!10!}=\frac N{1!18!}$$

$$=\frac 1{2\times 17!}+\frac 1{3\times 16!}+\frac 1{4\times 15!}+\frac 1{5\times 14!}+\frac 1{6\times 13!}+\frac 1{7\times 12!}+\frac 1{8\times 11!}+\frac 1{9\times 10!}=\frac N{1\times 18!}$$

$$=\frac 1{34}+\frac 1{48}+\frac 1{60}+\frac 1{70}+\frac 1{78}+\frac 1{84}+\frac 1{88}+\frac 1{81}=\frac N{18!}$$

$$=\frac {\frac 1{34}+\frac 1{48}+\frac 1{60}+\frac 1{70}+\frac 1{78}+\frac 1{84}+\frac 1{88}+\frac 1{81}}{\frac{1}{18!}}=\frac N{18!}$$

$$=\frac{18!\left ( \frac 1{34}+\frac 1{48}+\frac 1{60}+\frac 1{70}+\frac 1{78}+\frac 1{84}+\frac 1{88}+\frac 1{81} \right )}{18!}=\frac N{18!}$$

$$=\left ( \frac 1{34}+\frac 1{48}+\frac 1{60}+\frac 1{70}+\frac 1{78}+\frac 1{84}+\frac 1{88}+\frac 1{81} \right )=\frac N{18!}$$

$$=\frac{7335476032}{25852016738880000000}=\frac N{2.585\times 10^{19}}$$

$$\frac N{2.585\times 10^{19}}=283.75$$

$$\therefore \frac N{100}=283.75\times \frac{100}{2.585\times 10^{19}}$$

$$\frac N{100}=\frac{28375}{2.585\times 10^{19}}$$

$$\frac N{100}=\frac{28375}{25850000000000000}$$

$$\frac N{100}=1.1\times 10^{-13}$$

Therefore the greatest integer that is less than $\frac N{100}$ is $0$.
